import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['size'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='name', data=data, order=data['name'].value_counts().index, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?')
    plt.axvline(x=0, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
